-- Nestle board to consider acquisition Dec 7
-- 
-- Mon Nov 30, 2009 7:02am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/11/30/us-nestle-acquisition-idUSTRE5AT24M20091130

 

 MUMBAI  (Reuters) - Nestle India Ltd ( NEST.BO ) said on Monday its board will meet December 7 to consider unlisted Speciality Foods India's proposal to sell its healthcare nutrition business on mutually agreed terms. 

 The healthcare nutrition business's revenue for the year ended March 31, 2009, was 288 million rupees, Nestle said in a statement to the BSE. The product portfolio of business unit is meant to satisfy needs of consumers with special nutritional requirements and sold in India under brands "Resource", "Optifast" and "Spert", the statement added. (Reporting by Tamajit Pain; Editing by Harish Nambiar)